  6 /**
  7  * @ignore Just Inheritance Helper
  8  */
  9 Function.prototype.inheritsFrom = function( parentClassOrObject )
 10 {
 11     if ( parentClassOrObject.constructor == Function )
 12     {
 13         //Normal Inheritance
 14         this.prototype = new parentClassOrObject;
 15         this.prototype.constructor = this;
 16         this.prototype.parent = parentClassOrObject.prototype;
 17     }
 18     else
 19     {
 20         //Pure Virtual Inheritance
 21         this.prototype = parentClassOrObject;
 22         this.prototype.constructor = this;
 23         this.prototype.parent = parentClassOrObject;
 24     }
 25     return this;
 26 };

 45 /**
 46  * @ignore Helper for Events
 47  */
 48 EarthServerGenericClient.getEventTarget = function(e)
 49 {
 50     e = e || window.event;
 51     return e.target || e.srcElement;
 52 };

 54 /**
 55  * @class SceneManager is the main class of the unified client.
 56  * All scene models are registered in this class with the add() function.
 57  * The createScene() function creates a x3dom scene with all scene models.
 58  */
 59 EarthServerGenericClient.SceneManager = function()
 60 {
 61     /**
 62      * An Array of scene models.
 63      * @type {Array}
 64      * @default []
 65      */
 66     this.models = [];
 67     /**
 68      * An Array to store the models loading progress.
 69      * @type {Array}
 70      * @default []
 71      */
 72     this.modelLoadingProgress = [];
 73     /**
 74      * Value for the loading progress bar (all model loading combined).
 75      * @type {number}
 76      * @default 0
 77      */
 78     this.totalLoadingProgress = 0;
 79     /**
 80      * Every Model has it's base elevation on the Y-Axis. Needed to change and restore the elevation.
 81      * @type {Array}
 82      * @default []
 83      */
 84     this.baseElevation = [];
 85     /**
 86      * The current chosen UI element, which is a Model. Change everything for the model with that ID.
 87      * @type {number}
 88      * @default []
 89      */
 90     this.currentUIElement = 0;
 91     /**
 92      * Callback function for the progress update.
 93      * @type {undefined}
 94      * @default undefined
 95      */
 96     this.progressCallback = undefined;
 97 
 98     /**
 99      *
100      * @type {Array}
101      */
102     this.annotationLayers = [];      //Array of AnnotationsLayer to display annotations in the cube
103 
104     /**
105      * Enables/Disables the logging of Serverrequests,building of terrain etc.
106      * @default false
107      * @type {boolean}
108      */
109     this.TimeLog = false;
110 
111     /**
112      * This variable contains the AxisLabel object.
113      * This object manages the labels and its appearances on each axis.
114      * @default null
115      * @type {Object}
116      */
117     var axisLabels = null;
118 
119     /**
120      * Name of the X-Axis to be displayed.
121      * @default "x"
122      * @type {String}
123      */
124     this.xLabel = "X";
125 
126     /**
127      * Name of the Y-Axis to be displayed.
128      * @default "y"
129      * @type {String}

131     this.yLabel = "Y";
132 
133     /**
134      * Name of the Z-Axis to be displayed.
135      * @default "z"
136      * @type {String}
137      */
138     this.zLabel = "Z";
139 
140     /**
141      * Max resolution per dimension (standard PC)
142      * @default 1000 (200 on a mobile platform)
143      * @type {Number}
144      */
145     var maxResolution = 1000;
146     if( EarthServerGenericClient.isMobilePlatform())  //and for mobile Clients
147         maxResolution = 200;

149     /**
150      * Enables or disables the logging.
151      * @param value - Boolean
152      */
153     this.setTimeLog = function(value)
154     {   this.TimeLog = value; };
155     /**
156      * Starts the timer for a logging event with the given name.
157      * @param eventName
158      */
159     this.timeLogStart = function(eventName)
160     {
161         if( this.TimeLog)
162         {   console.time(eventName); }
163     };
164     /**
165      * Ends the timer for a logging event with the given name and prints the result.
166      * @param eventName
167      */
168     this.timeLogEnd = function(eventName)
169     {
170         if( this.TimeLog)
171         {   console.timeEnd(eventName); }
172     };

174     /**
175      * Returns the index of an existing AnnotationLayer in the array or -1 if no layer with the given name was found.
176      * @param AnnotationLayerName - Name of the Layer
177      * @returns {number} - Either index in the array or -1 if not found
178      */
179     this.getAnnotationLayerIndex = function(AnnotationLayerName)
180     {
181         for(var i=0;i<this.annotationLayers.length;i++)
182         {
183             if( this.annotationLayers[i].name === AnnotationLayerName)
184             {
185                 return i;
186             }
187         }
188 
189         return -1;
190     };
191 
192     /**
193      * Adds an AnnotationsLayer to the scene.
194      * @param name - Name of the Layer. You need the name of a layer to add annotations to it.
195      * @param fontSize - Font size of all annotations added to this layer.
196      * @param fontColor - Color of all annotations added to this layer.
197      * @param fontHover - The annotation text hovers above the annotation marker by this value.
198      * @param markerSize - The size if the annotation marker
199      * @param markerColor - Color of the annotation marker
200      */
201     this.addAnnotationsLayer = function(name,fontSize,fontColor,fontHover,markerSize,markerColor)
202     {
203         var root = document.getElementById("AnnotationsGroup");
204         if( root)
205         {
206             if( this.getAnnotationLayerIndex(name) < 0)
207             {
208                 var layer = new EarthServerGenericClient.AnnotationLayer(name,root,fontSize,fontColor,fontHover,markerSize,markerColor);
209                 this.annotationLayers.push(layer);
210             }
211             else
212             {   alert("AnnotationLayer with this name already created.");   }
213         }
214         else
215         {   alert("Please add Layers after creating the scene.");   }
216     };
217 
218     /**
219      * Adds an annotation to an existing annotation layer.
220      * @param AnnotationLayerName - Name of the annotation layer to add the annotation to.
221      * @param xPos - Position on the x-axis of the annotation.
222      * @param yPos - Position on the y-axis of the annotation.
223      * @param zPos - Position on the z-axis of the annotation.
224      * @param Text - Text of the annotation.
225      */
226     this.addAnnotation = function(AnnotationLayerName,xPos,yPos,zPos,Text)
227     {
228         var index = this.getAnnotationLayerIndex(AnnotationLayerName);
229         if( index >= 0)
230         {
231             this.annotationLayers[index].addAnnotation(xPos,yPos,zPos,Text);
232         }
233         else
234         {
235             alert("Could not found a AnnotationLayer with name: " + AnnotationLayerName);
236         }
237     };

239     /**
240      * Sets the callback function for the progress update. The progress function gives a parameter between 0-100.
241      * You can set callback = null for no progress update at all. If no callback is given at all the progress is
242      * printed to the console.
243      * @param callback
244      */
245     this.setProgressCallback=function(callback)
246     {
247         this.progressCallback = callback;
248     };
249     /**
250      * All Modules and Terrain shall report their loading progress.
251      * Modules when they receive data and terrains if they are done building the terrain.
252      * Every time this function is called 1 is added to the total progress. It is assumed that for every
253      * request a terrain is build thus 100% = model.requests*2
254      * If a callback is registered the function is called, otherwise the progress is printed to the console or ignored.
255      * @param modelIndex - Index of the model.
256      */
257     this.reportProgress = function(modelIndex)
258     {
259         //If null no progress update is wished
260         if( this.progressCallback !== null)
261         {
262             this.modelLoadingProgress[modelIndex] += 1;
263 
264             //Reset total loading progress to 0 and calc it with the new value
265             this.totalLoadingProgress = 0;
266             for(var i=0; i<this.modelLoadingProgress.length; i++)
267             {
268                 var tmp = this.modelLoadingProgress[i] / ( this.models[i].requests *2 );
269                 if( tmp > 1.0) tmp = 1;
270                 this.totalLoadingProgress += tmp;
271             }
272             this.totalLoadingProgress = (this.totalLoadingProgress / this.modelLoadingProgress.length)*100;
273 
274             //Callback function or console?
275             if( this.progressCallback !== undefined)
276             {   this.progressCallback(this.totalLoadingProgress);    }
277             else
278             {   console.log(this.totalLoadingProgress); }
279         }
280     };
281 
282     /**
283      * Returns the maximum resolution per dimension of a scene model.
284      * This number depends on power templates (e.g. mobile device).
285      * @return {Number}
286      */
287     this.getMaxResolution = function()
288     {   return maxResolution;   };

290     /**
291      * Adds any scene model to the scene.
292      * @param model
293      *      Any type of scene model.
294      */
295     this.addModel = function( model )
296     {
297         //Model ID is the current length of the models array. That means to IDs start at 0 and increase by 1.
298         model.modelID = this.models.length;
299         //Store model in the array
300         this.models.push(model);
301         //Initialize it's loading progress to 0
302         this.modelLoadingProgress[model.modelID] = 0;
303     };

305     /**
306      * Sets the view of the X3Dom window to the predefined camera.
307      * @param camID - ID of the Camera dom object.
308      */
309     this.setView =function(camID)
310     {
311         var cam = document.getElementById(camID);
312         if(cam)
313         {
314             //If the user changes the camera, then moves around the camera has to be set to false to be able to bin again
315             cam.setAttribute('set_bind','false');
316             cam.setAttribute('set_bind','true');
317         }
318     };

320     /**
321      * Creates and returns the whole X3DOM Scene in the fishtank/cube with all added scene models.
322      * The Sizes of the cube are assumed as aspect ratios with values between 0 and 1.
323      * Example createScene("x3dom_div",1.0, 0.3, 0.5 ) Cube has 30% height and 50 depth compared to the width.
324      * @param x3dID - ID of the x3d dom element
325      * @param sceneID - ID of the scene element
326      * @param cubeSizeX - width of the cube
327      * @param cubeSizeY - height of the cube
328      * @param cubeSizeZ - depth of the cube
329      */
330     this.createScene = function(x3dID,sceneID, cubeSizeX, cubeSizeY, cubeSizeZ )
331     {
332         if( cubeSizeX <= 0 || cubeSizeX > 1.0) cubeSizeX = 1.0;
333         if( cubeSizeY <= 0 || cubeSizeY > 1.0) cubeSizeY = 1.0;
334         if( cubeSizeZ <= 0 || cubeSizeZ > 1.0) cubeSizeZ = 1.0;
335 
336         cubeSizeX = (parseFloat(cubeSizeX) * 1000);
337         cubeSizeY = (parseFloat(cubeSizeY) * 1000);
338         cubeSizeZ = (parseFloat(cubeSizeZ) * 1000);
339 
340         this.cubeSizeX = cubeSizeX;
341         this.cubeSizeY = cubeSizeY;
342         this.cubeSizeZ = cubeSizeZ;
343 
344         var scene = document.getElementById(sceneID);
345         if( !scene)
346         {
347             alert("No X3D Scene found with id " + sceneID);
348             return;
349         }
350 
351         //Cameras
352         var cam1 = document.createElement('Viewpoint');
353         cam1.setAttribute("id","EarthServerGenericClient_Cam_Front");
354         cam1.setAttribute("position", "0 0 " + this.cubeSizeZ*2);
355         var cam2 = document.createElement('Viewpoint');
356         cam2.setAttribute("id","EarthServerGenericClient_Cam_Top");
357         cam2.setAttribute("position", "0 " + this.cubeSizeY*2.5 + " 0");
358         cam2.setAttribute("orientation", "1.0 0.0 0.0 -1.55");
359         var cam3 = document.createElement('Viewpoint');
360         cam3.setAttribute("id","EarthServerGenericClient_Cam_Side");
361         cam3.setAttribute("position", "" + -this.cubeSizeX*2+ " 0 0");
362         cam3.setAttribute("orientation", "0 1 0 -1.55");
363         scene.appendChild(cam1);
364         scene.appendChild(cam2);
365         scene.appendChild(cam3);
366 
367         var buttonTopView = document.createElement('button');
368         buttonTopView.setAttribute("id","EarthServerGenericClient_Button_TopView");
369         buttonTopView.setAttribute("class", "inside");
370         buttonTopView.setAttribute("onclick", "EarthServerGenericClient_MainScene.setView('EarthServerGenericClient_Cam_Top');return false;");
371         buttonTopView.innerHTML = "TopView";
372         scene.appendChild(buttonTopView);
373         var buttonFrontView = document.createElement('button');
374         buttonFrontView.setAttribute("id","EarthServerGenericClient_Button_FrontView");
375         buttonFrontView.setAttribute("class", "inside");
376         buttonFrontView.setAttribute("onclick", "EarthServerGenericClient_MainScene.setView('EarthServerGenericClient_Cam_Front');return false;");
377         buttonFrontView.innerHTML = "FrontView";
378         scene.appendChild(buttonFrontView);
379         var buttonSideView = document.createElement('button');
380         buttonSideView.setAttribute("id","EarthServerGenericClient_Button_SideView");
381         buttonSideView.setAttribute("class", "inside");
382         buttonSideView.setAttribute("onclick", "EarthServerGenericClient_MainScene.setView('EarthServerGenericClient_Cam_Side');return false;");
383         buttonSideView.innerHTML = "SideView";
384         scene.appendChild(buttonSideView);
385 
386         var shape = document.createElement('Shape');
387         var appearance = document.createElement('Appearance');
388         var material = document.createElement('Material');
389         material.setAttribute("emissiveColor","1 1 0");
390 
391         var lineset = document.createElement('IndexedLineSet');
392         lineset.setAttribute("colorPerVertex", "false");
393         lineset.setAttribute("coordIndex","0 1 2 3 0 -1 4 5 6 7 4 -1 0 4 -1 1 5 -1 2 6 -1 3 7 -1");
394 
395         var coords = document.createElement('Coordinate');
396         coords.setAttribute("id", "cube");
397 
398         var cubeX = cubeSizeX/2.0;
399         var cubeY = cubeSizeY/2.0;
400         var cubeZ = cubeSizeZ/2.0;
401         var cubeXNeg = -cubeSizeX/2.0;
402         var cubeYNeg = -cubeSizeY/2.0;
403         var cubeZNeg = -cubeSizeZ/2.0;
404 
405         var p = {};
406         p[0] = ""+ cubeXNeg + " " + cubeYNeg + " " + cubeZNeg + " ";
407         p[1] = ""+ cubeX + " " + cubeYNeg + " " + cubeZNeg + " ";
408         p[2] = ""+ cubeX + " " + cubeY + " " + cubeZNeg + " ";
409         p[3] = ""+ cubeXNeg + " " + cubeY + " " + cubeZNeg + " ";
410         p[4] = ""+ cubeXNeg + " " + cubeYNeg + " " + cubeZ + " ";
411         p[5] = ""+ cubeX + " " + cubeYNeg + " " + cubeZ + " ";
412         p[6] = ""+ cubeX + " " + cubeY + " " + cubeZ + " ";
413         p[7] = ""+ cubeXNeg + " " + cubeY + " " + cubeZ + " ";
414         var points="";
415         for(var i=0; i<8;i++)
416         {   points = points+p[i];   }
417         coords.setAttribute("point", points);
418 
419         lineset.appendChild(coords);
420         appearance.appendChild(material);
421         shape.appendChild(appearance);
422         shape.appendChild(lineset);
423         scene.appendChild(shape);
424 
425         var trans = document.createElement('Transform');
426         trans.setAttribute("id", "trans");
427         scene.appendChild(trans);
428 
429         this.setView('EarthServerGenericClient_Cam_Front');
430         this.trans = trans;
431 
432         var annotationTrans = document.createElement("transform");
433         annotationTrans.setAttribute("id","AnnotationsGroup");
434         scene.appendChild(annotationTrans);
435     };

457     /**
458      * Update Offset changes the position of the current selected SceneModel on the x-,y- or z-Axis.
459      * @param which - Which Axis will be changed (0:X 1:Y 2:Z)
460      * @param value - The new position
461      */
462     this.updateOffset = function(which,value)
463     {
464         var trans = document.getElementById("EarthServerGenericClient_modelTransform"+this.currentUIElement);
465 
466         if( trans )
467         {
468             var offset;
469             switch(which)
470             {
471                 case 0: offset = this.cubeSizeX/2.0; break;
472                 case 1: offset = this.cubeSizeY/2.0; break;
473                 case 2: offset = this.cubeSizeZ/2.0; break;
474             }
475             var oldTrans = trans.getAttribute("translation");
476             oldTrans = oldTrans.split(" ");
477             oldTrans[which] = value - offset;
478             trans.setAttribute("translation",oldTrans[0] + " " + oldTrans[1] + " " + oldTrans[2]);
479         }
480     };
481 
482     /**
483      * This changes the scaling on the Y-Axis(Elevation).
484      * @param value - The base elevation is multiplied by this value
485      */
486     this.updateElevation =function(value)
487     {
488         var trans = document.getElementById("EarthServerGenericClient_modelTransform"+this.currentUIElement);
489 
490         if( trans )
491         {
492             var oldTrans = trans.getAttribute("scale");
493             oldTrans = oldTrans.split(" ");
494 
495             if( this.baseElevation[this.currentUIElement] === undefined)
496             {
497                 this.baseElevation[this.currentUIElement] = oldTrans[1];
498             }
499 
500             oldTrans[1] = value*this.baseElevation[this.currentUIElement]/10;
501 
502             trans.setAttribute("scale",oldTrans[0] + " " + oldTrans[1] + " " + oldTrans[2]);
503         }
504     };
505 
506     /**
507      * Changes the transparency of the Scene Model.
508      * @param value - New Transparency between 0-1 (Fully Opaque - Fully Transparent)
509      */
510     this.updateTransparency = function(value)
511     {
512         this.models[this.currentUIElement].updateTransparency(value);
513     };

515     /**
516      * This creates the UI for the Scene.
517      * @param domElementID - The dom element where to append the UI.
518      */
519     this.createUI = function(domElementID)
520     {
521         var mytable = document.createElement("table");
522         var mytablebody = document.createElement("tbody");
523         mytable.appendChild(mytablebody);
524 
525         var Element = document.getElementById(domElementID);
526         if(Element)
527         {   Element.appendChild(mytable);}
528         else
529         {   alert("Can't find DOM Element with ID: " + domElementID);   }
530 
531 
532         var mycurrent_row=document.createElement("tr");
533         mytablebody.appendChild(mycurrent_row);
534 
535         var mycurrent_cell = document.createElement("th");
536         mycurrent_cell.innerHTML = "Modules";
537         mycurrent_row.appendChild(mycurrent_cell);
538         mycurrent_cell = document.createElement("th");
539         mycurrent_cell.innerHTML = "Common";
540         mycurrent_row.appendChild(mycurrent_cell);
541         mycurrent_cell = document.createElement("th");
542         mycurrent_cell.innerHTML = "Specific";
543         mycurrent_row.appendChild(mycurrent_cell);
544 
545 
546         //Cell 1: List with all modules
547         mycurrent_row=document.createElement("tr");
548         mycurrent_cell = document.createElement("td");
549         var module_list = document.createElement("ul");
550         module_list.setAttribute("id", "UI_ModuleList");
551         module_list.onclick = function(event) {
552             var target = EarthServerGenericClient.getEventTarget(event);
553             var UIID = target.id;
554             UIID = UIID.split(":");
555             EarthServerGenericClient_MainScene.currentUIElement = UIID[2];
556 
557             //Set all style to none
558             for (var i = 0; i < EarthServerGenericClient_MainScene.models.length; i++)
559             {
560                 var div = document.getElementById("EarthServerGenericClient_SliderDiv_" +i);
561                 div.style.display = "none";
562                 div = document.getElementById("EarthServerGenericClient_SPECIFICDiv_" + i);
563                 div.style.display = "none";
564             }
565             //Set the chosen one to be shown
566             var theDiv = document.getElementById("EarthServerGenericClient_SliderDiv_" + EarthServerGenericClient_MainScene.currentUIElement);
567             theDiv.setAttribute("class", "active");
568             theDiv.style.display = "block";
569             theDiv = document.getElementById("EarthServerGenericClient_SPECIFICDiv_" + EarthServerGenericClient_MainScene.currentUIElement);
570             theDiv.setAttribute("class", "active");
571             theDiv.style.display = "block";
572 
573         };
574 
575         for (i = 0; i < this.models.length; i++)
576         {
577             var module = document.createElement("li");
578             module.setAttribute("id", "EarthServerGenericClient:MODULE:"+i);
579             module.innerHTML= this.models[i].name;
580             module_list.appendChild(module);
581         }
582 
583         mycurrent_cell.appendChild(module_list);
584         mycurrent_row.appendChild(mycurrent_cell);
585         mytablebody.appendChild(mycurrent_row);
586 
587         //Cell 2: Slider for the positioning X-Y-Z Axis
588         mycurrent_cell = document.createElement("td");
589         mycurrent_cell.setAttribute("id","EarthServerGenericClient_SliderCell");
590         mycurrent_row.appendChild(mycurrent_cell);
591 
592         for (i = 0; i < this.models.length; i++)
593         {
594             var modelDiv = document.createElement("div");
595             modelDiv.setAttribute("id","EarthServerGenericClient_SliderDiv_" + i);
596             modelDiv.style.display = "none";
597             mycurrent_cell.appendChild(modelDiv);
598 
599             EarthServerGenericClient.appendXYZASlider(modelDiv,i);
600         }
601 
602         //Cell 4: Some specific stuff
603         mycurrent_cell = document.createElement("td");
604         mycurrent_cell.setAttribute("id","EarthServerGenericClient_SPECIFIC_Cell");
605         mycurrent_row.appendChild(mycurrent_cell);
606 
607         for (var i = 0; i < this.models.length; i++)
608         {
609             var modelDiv = document.createElement("div");
610             modelDiv.setAttribute("id","EarthServerGenericClient_SPECIFICDiv_" + i);
611             modelDiv.style.display = "none";
612             mycurrent_cell.appendChild(modelDiv);
613 
614             this.models[i].setSpecificElement(modelDiv,i);
615         }
616 
617         //Make div 1 active
618         var div1 = document.getElementById("EarthServerGenericClient_SliderDiv_0");
619         div1.setAttribute("class", "active");
620         div1.style.display = "block";
621         div1 = document.getElementById("EarthServerGenericClient_SPECIFICDiv_0");
622         div1.setAttribute("class", "active");
623         div1.style.display = "block";
624     };

628      * @param xLabel - width
629      * @param yLabel - height
630      * @param zLabel - depth
631      */
632     this.setAxisLabels = function( xLabel, yLabel, zLabel){
633         this.xLabel = String(xLabel);
634         this.yLabel = String(yLabel);
635         this.zLabel = String(zLabel);

641 /**
642  * @class Abstract base class for scene models.
643  */
644 EarthServerGenericClient.AbstractSceneModel = function(){
645     /**
646      * Sets the name of the scene model.
647      * The name is useful for the demo because it appears in the category "Modules".
648      * @param modelName
649      *      Sets the name of model.
650      */
651     this.setName = function(modelName){
652         this.name = String(modelName);
653     };
654     /**
655      * Sets the area of interest for the model (Lower Corner, Upper Corner).
656      * @param minx
657      *      Minimum of lower latitude
658      * @param miny
659      *      Minimum of lower longitude
660      * @param maxx
661      *      Maximum of upper latitude
662      * @param maxy
663      *      Maximum of upper longitude
664      */
665     this.setAreaOfInterest = function(minx,miny,maxx,maxy){
666         this.minx = minx;
667         this.miny = miny;
668         this.maxx = maxx;
669         this.maxy = maxy;
670     };
671     /**
672      * Sets the resolution of the scene model (if possible).
673      * @param xRes
674      *      Resolution on the x-axis/Latitude
675      * @param zRes
676      *      Resolution on the z-axis/Longitude
677      */
678     this.setResolution = function(xRes,zRes){
679         this.XResolution = parseInt(xRes);
680         this.ZResolution = parseInt(zRes);
681 
682         var maxResolution = EarthServerGenericClient_MainScene.getMaxResolution();
683         if( this.XResolution > maxResolution )
684         {   this.XResolution = maxResolution;   }
685         if( this.ZResolution > maxResolution )
686         {   this.ZResolution = maxResolution;   }
687 
688     };
689 
690     /**
691      * Sets the position of the scene model within the fishtank/cube.
692      * The function accepts values in the range of 0 and 1 for each parameter.
693      * @param xOffset
694      *      Offset on the x-axis (width).
695      * @param yOffset
696      *      Offset on the y-axis (height).
697      * @param zOffset
698      *      Offset on the z-axis (depth).
699      */
700     this.setOffset = function( xOffset, yOffset, zOffset){
701         this.xOffset = parseFloat(xOffset);
702         this.yOffset = parseFloat(yOffset);
703         this.zOffset = parseFloat(zOffset);
704     };
705     /**
706      * Sets the size of the scene model compared to the fishtank/cube.
707      * The function accepts values in the range of 0 and 1 for each parameter.
708      * @param xScale
709      *      Size of the model on the x-axis (width).
710      * @param yScale
711      *      Size of the model on the y-axis (height).
712      * @param zScale
713      *      Size of the model on the x-axis (width).
714      */
715     this.setScale = function( xScale, yScale, zScale){
716         this.xScale = parseFloat(xScale);
717         this.yScale = parseFloat(yScale);
718         this.zScale = parseFloat(zScale);
719     };
720 
721     /**
722      * Sets the image format for the server request.
723      * @param imageFormat
724      *      Default format is "png".
725      */
726     this.setImageFormat = function( imageFormat){
727         this.imageFormat = String(imageFormat);
728     };
729 
730     /**
731      * Sets the initial transparency of the scene model.
732      * The function accepts a parameter value in the range of 0 (fully opaque) and 1(fully transparent).
733      * @param transparency
734      *      Value of visibility.
735      */
736     this.setTransparency = function( transparency ){
737         this.transparency = parseFloat(transparency);
738     };
739 
740     /**
741      * Updates the transparency during runtime of the scene model.
742      * The function accepts a value in the range of 0 (fully opaque) and 1(fully transparent).
743      * @param transparency
744      */
745     this.updateTransparency = function( transparency ){
746         this.terrain.setTransparency(transparency);
747     };
748 
749     /**
750      * Modules report their loading progress to this function which leads the information to the main scene.
751      */
752     this.reportProgress = function()
753     {
754         //The total progress of this module depens on the number of requests it does.
755         //The progress parameter is the progress of ONE request.
756         //ReceivedDataCount is the number of already received responses.
757         //it is doubled because for each request one terrain will be build.
758         var totalProgress = ((this.receivedDataCount) / (this.requests * 2))*100;
759         EarthServerGenericClient_MainScene.reportProgress(this.modelID,totalProgress);
760     };
761 
762     /**
763      * Validates the received data from the server request.
764      * Checks if a texture and a heightmap are available at the moment.
765      * @param data - Received data from the server request.
766      * @returns {boolean} - TRUE if OK, FALSE if some data is missing
767      */
768     this.checkReceivedData = function( data)
769     {
770         this.receivedDataCount++;
771         this.reportProgress();
772 
773         if( data === null || !data.validate() )
774         {
775             alert(this.name +": Request not successful.");
776             this.reportProgress();//NO Terrain will be built so report the progress here
777             this.removePlaceHolder();//Remove the placeHolder.
778             return false;
779         }
780 
781         return true;
782     };
783 
784     /**
785      * This creates a placeholder Element for the model. It consists of an simple quad.
786      * Models that use this placeholder should remove it of course.
787      */
788     this.createPlaceHolder = function()
789     {
790         var appearance = document.createElement('Appearance');
791         var material = document.createElement('Material');
792         material.setAttribute("emissiveColor","0.4 0.4 0.4");
793 
794         var trans = document.createElement('Transform');
795         var yoff = (this.cubeSizeY * this.yOffset);
796         trans.setAttribute("translation", "0 "+ yoff  + " 0");
797 
798         var shape = document.createElement('shape');
799         var triangleset = document.createElement('IndexedFaceSet');
800         triangleset.setAttribute("colorPerVertex", "false");
801         triangleset.setAttribute("coordindex","0 1 2 3 -1");
802 
803         var coords = document.createElement('Coordinate');
804 
805         var cubeX = this.cubeSizeX/2.0;
806         var cubeZ = this.cubeSizeZ/2.0;
807         var cubeXNeg = -this.cubeSizeX/2.0;
808         var cubeYNeg = -this.cubeSizeY/2.0;
809         var cubeZNeg = -this.cubeSizeZ/2.0;
810 
811         var p = {};
812         p[0] = ""+ cubeXNeg + " " + cubeYNeg + " " + cubeZNeg + " ";
813         p[1] = ""+ cubeXNeg + " " + cubeYNeg + " " + cubeZ + " ";
814         p[2] = ""+ cubeX    + " " + cubeYNeg + " " + cubeZ    + " ";
815         p[3] = ""+ cubeX    + " " + cubeYNeg + " " + cubeZNeg;
816 
817         var points="";
818         for(var i=0; i<4;i++)
819         {   points = points+p[i];   }
820         coords.setAttribute("point", points);
821 
822         triangleset.appendChild(coords);
823         appearance.appendChild(material);
824         shape.appendChild(appearance);
825         shape.appendChild(triangleset);
826         trans.appendChild(shape);
827 
828         this.placeHolder = trans;
829         this.root.appendChild( this.placeHolder );
830 
831         appearance = null;
832         material = null;
833         shape = null;
834         triangleset = null;
835         coords = null;
836         points = null;
837         trans = null;
838     };
839 
840     /**
841      * Removes the PlaceHolder created in createPlaceHolder(). If already deleted nothing happens.
842      */
843     this.removePlaceHolder = function()
844     {
845         if( this.placeHolder !== null && this.placeHolder !== undefined )
846         {
847             this.root.removeChild( this.placeHolder);
848             this.placeHolder = null;
849         }
850     };
851 
852     /**
853      * Creates the transform for the scene model to fit into the fishtank/cube. This is done automatically by
854      * the scene model.
855      * @param xRes
856      *      Size of the received data on the x-axis (e.g. the requested DEM )
857      * @param yRes
858      *      Size of the received data on the y-axis
859      * @param zRes
860      *      Size of the received data on the z-axis
861      * @param minvalue
862      *      Minimum Value along the y-axis (e.g. minimum value in a DEM, so the model starts at it's wished location)
863      * @return {Element}
864      */
865     this.createTransform = function(xRes,yRes,zRes,minvalue){
866         var trans = document.createElement('Transform');
867         trans.setAttribute("id", "EarthServerGenericClient_modelTransform"+this.modelID);
868 
869         this.YResolution = yRes;
870 
871         var scaleX = (this.cubeSizeX*this.xScale)/(parseInt(xRes)-1);
872         var scaleY = (this.cubeSizeY*this.yScale)/this.YResolution;
873         var scaleZ = (this.cubeSizeZ*this.zScale)/(parseInt(zRes)-1);
874         trans.setAttribute("scale", "" + scaleX + " " + scaleY + " " + scaleZ);
875 
876         var xoff = (this.cubeSizeX * this.xOffset) - (this.cubeSizeX/2.0);
877         var yoff = (this.cubeSizeY * this.yOffset) - (minvalue*scaleY) - (this.cubeSizeY/2.0);
878         var zoff = (this.cubeSizeZ * this.zOffset) - (this.cubeSizeZ/2.0);
879         trans.setAttribute("translation", "" + xoff+ " " + yoff  + " " + zoff);
880 
881         return trans;
882     };

892         this.name = "No name given";
893 
894         /**
895          * Resolution for the latitude.
896          * @default 500
897          * @type {Number}
898          */
899         this.XResolution = 500;
900 
901         /**
902          * Resolution for the longitude
903          * @default 500
904          * @type {Number}
905          */
906         this.ZResolution = 500;
907 
908         /**
909          * Offset on the X-Axis for the model.
910          * @default 0
911          * @type {Number}
912          */
913         this.xOffset = 0;
914 
915         /**
916          * Offset on the Y-Axis for the model.
917          * @default 0
918          * @type {Number}
919          */
920         this.yOffset = 0;
921

923          * Offset on the Z-Axis for the model.
924          * @default 0

927         this.zOffset = 0;

930          * The models dimension compared to the whole cube on the X-Axis.

934         this.xScale = 1;
935

937          * The models dimension compared to the whole cube on the Y-Axis.
938          * @default 0.3
939          * @type {Number}
940          */
941         this.yScale = 0.3;
942

944          * The models dimension compared to the whole cube on the Z-Axis.
945          * @default 1
946          * @type {Number}
947          */
948         this.zScale = 1;
949 
950         /**
951          * The used Image format (if one is used)
952          * @default "png"
953          * @type {String}
954          */
955         this.imageFormat = "png";
956 
957         /**
958          * The amount of requests the model do. It is needed to keep track of the loading progress.
959          * @default 1

962         this.requests = 1;

969         this.receivedDataCount = 0;
970 
971         /**
972          * The Transparency of the model.

974          * @type {Number}
975          */
976         this.transparency = 0;

981 /**
982  * @class AxisLabels
983  * @description This class generates labels for each axis and side (except bottom) of the bounding box.
984  *
985  * @param xSize
986  *      The width of the bounding box.
987  * @param ySize
988  *      The height of the bounding box.
989  * @param zSize
990  *      The depth of the bounding box.
991  */
992 EarthServerGenericClient.AxisLabels = function(xSize, ySize, zSize)
993 {
994     /**
995      * @description Defines the color of the text. Default at start: emissiveColor attribute is set, the diffuseColor one isn't.
996      * @type {string}
997      * @default "0.7 0.7 0.5"
998      */
999     var fontColor = "0.7 0.7 0.5";
1000 
1001     /**
1002      * @description Defines the size of the font. Value is always positive!
1003      * @default 50.0
1004      * @type {number}
1005      */
1006     var fontSize = 50.0;
1007 
1008     /**
1009      * @description Array stores all X3DOM transform nodes. Each transform contains the shape, material, text and fontStyle node.
1010      * @type {Array}
1011      * @default Empty
1012      */
1013     var transforms = new Array();
1014     /**
1015      * @description Array stores all text nodes of the x-axis.
1016      * @type {Array}
1017      * @default Empty
1018      */
1019     var textNodesX = new Array();
1020     /**
1021      * @description Array stores all text nodes of the y-axis.
1022      * @type {Array}
1023      * @default Empty
1024      */
1025     var textNodesY = new Array();
1026     /**
1027      * @description Array stores all text nodes of the z-axis.
1028      * @type {Array}
1029      * @default Empty
1030      */
1031     var textNodesZ = new Array();
1032 
1033     /**
1034      * @description This function changes the text size of each label independent of its axis.
1035      *
1036      * @param size
1037      * The parameter (positive value expected) represents the desired size of the font.
1038      * Remember, the parameter represents the size in x3dom units not in pt like css.
1039      * Hence the size value could be large.
1040      */
1041     this.changeFontSize = function(size)
1042     {
1043         size = Math.abs(size);
1044         for(var i=0; i<transforms.length; i++)
1045         {
1046             var scale =x3dom.fields.SFVec3f.parse(transforms[i].getAttribute('scale'));
1047 
1048             if(scale.x>=0) scale.x = size; else scale.x = -1 * size;
1049             if(scale.y>=0) scale.y = size; else scale.y = -1 * size;
1050             if(scale.z>=0) scale.z = size; else scale.z = -1 * size;
1051 
1052             transforms[i].setAttribute('scale', scale.x + " " + scale.y + " " + scale.z);
1053         }
1054     };
1055 
1056     /**
1057      * This function changes the color of each label independent of its axis.
1058      * @param color
1059      * This parameter changes the current color value of each label.
1060      * It expects a string in x3d color format.
1061      * E.g. "1.0 1.0 1.0" for white and "0.0 0.0 0.0" for black.
1062      */
1063     this.changeColor = function(color)
1064     {
1065         for(var i=0; i<transforms.length; i++)
1066         {
1067             var material = transforms[i].getElementsByTagName('material');
1068 
1069             for(var j=0; j<material.length; j++)
1070             {
1071                 material[j].setAttribute('emissiveColor', color);
1072                 material[j].setAttribute('diffuseColor', color);
1073             }
1074         }
1075     };
1076 
1077     /**
1078      * @description This function changes the text of each label on the x-axis.
1079      *
1080      * @param string
1081      * Defines the new text.
1082      */
1083     this.changeLabelNameX = function(string)
1084     {
1085         //Prevent multi line!
1086         while(string.search("'")!=-1 || string.search("\"")!=-1)
1087         {
1088             string = string.replace("'", " ");
1089             string = string.replace("\"", " ");
1090         }
1091 
1092         for(var i=0; i<textNodesX.length; i++)
1093         {
1094             textNodesX[i].setAttribute('string', string);
1095         }
1096     };
1097 
1098     /**
1099      * @description This function changes the text of each label on the y-axis.
1100      *
1101      * @param string
1102      * Defines the new text.
1103      */
1104     this.changeLabelNameY = function(string)
1105     {
1106         //Prevent multi line!
1107         while(string.search("'")!=-1 || string.search("\"")!=-1)
1108         {
1109             string = string.replace("'", " ");
1110             string = string.replace("\"", " ");
1111         }
1112 
1113         for(var i=0; i<textNodesY.length; i++)
1114         {
1115             textNodesY[i].setAttribute('string', string);
1116         }
1117     };
1118 
1119     /**
1120      * @param string
1121      * Defines the new text.
1122      */
1123     this.changeLabelNameZ = function(string)
1124     {
1125         //Prevent multi line!
1126         while(string.search("'")!=-1 || string.search("\"")!=-1)
1127         {
1128             string = string.replace("'", " ");
1129             string = string.replace("\"", " ");
1130         }
1131 
1132         for(var i=0; i<textNodesZ.length; i++)
1133         {
1134             textNodesZ[i].setAttribute('string', string);
1135         }
1136     };
1137 
1138     /**
1139      * @description This function generates labels on all three axis (x,y,z). The labels will be
1140      * added on each side (except bottom).
1141      */
1142     this.createAxisLabels = function(xLabel,yLabel,zLabel)
1143     {
1144         createLabel("x", "front", xLabel);
1145         createLabel("x", "back",  xLabel);
1146         createLabel("x", "top",   xLabel);
1147 
1148         createLabel("y", "front", yLabel);
1149         createLabel("y", "back",  yLabel);
1150         createLabel("y", "left",  yLabel);
1151         createLabel("y", "right", yLabel);
1152 
1153         createLabel("z", "front", zLabel);
1154         createLabel("z", "back",  zLabel);
1155         createLabel("z", "top",   zLabel);
1156     };
1157 
1158     /**
1159      * @description This (private) function creates the needed x3dom nodes.
1160      *
1161      * @param axis
1162      * Which axis do you want? Available: x, y, z
1163      *
1164      * @param side
1165      * Choose the side of the axis. <br>
1166      * Available for x: front (default), back and top. <br>
1167      * Available for y: front (default), back, left and right. <br>
1168      * Available for z: front (default), back and top.
1169      *
1170      * @param label
1171      * This text will appear at the given axis.
1172      */
1173     function createLabel(axis, side, label)
1174     {
1175         //Setup text
1176         var textTransform = document.createElement('transform');
1177         textTransform.setAttribute('scale', fontSize + " " + fontSize + " " + fontSize);
1178         var shape = document.createElement('shape');
1179         var appearance = document.createElement('appearance');
1180         var material = document.createElement('material');
1181         material.setAttribute('emissiveColor', fontColor);
1182         var text = document.createElement('text');
1183         text.setAttribute('string', label);
1184         var fontStyle = document.createElement('fontStyle');
1185         fontStyle.setAttribute('family', 'calibri');
1186         fontStyle.setAttribute('style', 'bold');
1187         text.appendChild(fontStyle);
1188         appearance.appendChild(material);
1189         shape.appendChild(appearance);
1190         shape.appendChild(text);
1191         textTransform.appendChild(shape);
1192 
1193         //var home = document.getElementById('x3dScene');
1194         var home = document.getElementById('AnnotationsGroup');
1195         var rotationTransform = document.createElement('transform');
1196 
1197         if(axis=="x")
1198         {
1199             textTransform.setAttribute('translation', "0 " + (ySize+fontSize/2) + " " + zSize);
1200 
1201             if(side=="back")
1202             {
1203                 rotationTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '0 1 0 3.14');
1204             }
1205             else if(side=="top")
1206             {
1207                 textTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '1 0 0 -1.57');
1208                 textTransform.setAttribute('translation', "0 " + -ySize + " " + (-zSize-fontSize/2));
1209             }
1210             textNodesX[textNodesX.length] = text;
1211         }
1212         else if(axis=="y")
1213         {
1214             textTransform.setAttribute('translation', -(xSize+fontSize/2) + " 0 " + zSize);
1215             textTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '0 0 1 1.57');
1216 
1217             if(side=="back")
1218             {
1219                 textTransform.setAttribute('translation', (xSize+fontSize/2) + " 0 " + zSize);
1220                 textTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '0 0 1 4.74');
1221                 rotationTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '1 0 0 3.14');
1222             }
1223             else if(side=="left")
1224             {
1225                 rotationTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '0 1 0 -1.57');
1226             }
1227             else if(side=="right")
1228             {
1229                 rotationTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '0 1 0 1.57');
1230             }
1231             textNodesY[textNodesY.length] = text;
1232         }
1233         else if(axis=="z")
1234         {
1235             textTransform.setAttribute('translation', xSize + " " + (ySize+fontSize/2) + " 0");
1236             textTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '0 1 0 1.57');
1237             if(side=="back")
1238             {
1239                 rotationTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '0 1 0 3.14');
1240             }
1241             else if(side=="top")
1242             {
1243                 textTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '0 1 0 1.57');
1244                 textTransform.setAttribute('translation', "0 0 0");
1245 
1246                 rotationTransform.setAttribute('rotation', '0 0 1 -4.71');
1247                 rotationTransform.setAttribute('translation', -(xSize+fontSize/2) + " " + -ySize + " 0");
1248             }
1249             textNodesZ[textNodesZ.length] = text;
1250         }
1251 
1252         transforms[transforms.length]=textTransform;
1253         rotationTransform.appendChild(textTransform);
1254         home.appendChild(rotationTransform);
1255     }
1256 };
